<item>
            <title>[HIVE-29307] Incorrect split calculation causing less container to launch</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-29307</link>
                <project id="12310843" key="HIVE">Hive</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/hive/blob/6b5febcc559e9f20ebea6fb04679477cf125144f/ql/src/java/org/apache/hadoop/hive/ql/exec/tez/HiveSplitGenerator.java#L363&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/hive/blob/6b5febcc559e9f20ebea6fb04679477cf125144f/ql/src/java/org/apache/hadoop/hive/ql/exec/tez/HiveSplitGenerator.java#L363&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
splits = inputFormat.getSplits(jobConf, numSplits.orElse(&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Math&lt;/span&gt;.multiplyExact(availableSlots, (&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;)waves))); &lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Type casting of waves i.e. from float to int is causing less number of container launch&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As good value of waves should be 1.7, 2.7, 3.7 etc as per &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/tez/blob/5775337a5be3993d1aeb9b4c39134fe96c9b39f2/tez-mapreduce/src/main/java/org/apache/tez/mapreduce/grouper/TezSplitGrouper.java#L62&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/tez/blob/5775337a5be3993d1aeb9b4c39134fe96c9b39f2/tez-mapreduce/src/main/java/org/apache/tez/mapreduce/grouper/TezSplitGrouper.java#L62&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This incorrect calcutation will interfere with the org.apache.tez.mapreduce.grouper.TezSplitGrouper class.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
